      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2017-04-11 14:00:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAndreas – I understand and agree that the sanity-lfsck test suite is skipped if run with clients and servers with different versions of Lustre. Right now, running sanity-lfsck in any Lustre configuration (interop or otherwise), tests 9a and 9b are being skipped due to the version check at the beginning of the tests because we never initialize the server_version variable:\n[[ $server_version -ge $(version_code 2.7.50) ]] ||\n\t\t{ skip \"Need MDS version >= 2.7.50\"; return; }\n\nThe purpose of this patch is to remove the server check at the beginning of test 9a and 9b to allow the tests to run.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
